-- Tourist Spending in Greece Rises 9.7% on Surge in Visitors
-- B y   M a r c u s   B e n s a s s o n
-- 2012-01-24T13:07:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/tourist-spending-in-greece-rises-9-7-on-surge-in-visitors.html
Spending by visitors to  Greece  in
the first 11 months of 2011 was 9.7 percent higher than a year
earlier as the number of tourists increased.  Tourism receipts from January to November reached 10.4
billion euros ($13.5 billion), up from 9.5 billion euros in the
comparable period of 2010, according to an e-mailed statement
from the  Bank of Greece . Visitors increased 9.6 percent.  Revenue in November was 185 million euros, 12.5 percent
less than in the same month a year earlier, according to the
statement.  Tourism accounts for about 16 percent of Greeceâ€™s gross
domestic product, according to the London-based  World Travel and
Tourism Council .  To contact the reporter on this story:
